{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:50:28.697Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"jdi0i9bl","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/README.md","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Local MVP Backend Foundation\n  2 | \n  3 | Welcome to the local FastAPI MVP backend foundation for the GFF AI Enterprise platform. This module provides local developer API capabilities, SQLite storage connectivity, system health monitoring, and a fully configured local CORS workspace to interface seamlessly with the Next.js frontend.\n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## Architecture Overview\n  8 | \n  9 | The backend uses a standard, modular clean-architecture layout built for Python 3.12+ and FastAPI:\n 10 | \n 11 | ```text\n 12 | backend/\n 13 | ├── app/\n 14 | │   ├── __init__.py\n 15 | │   ├── api.py           # Core endpoints (Health, SystemLogs)\n 16 | │   ├── config.py        # Settings & Pydantic Config Validation\n 17 | │   ├── database.py      # SQLAlchemy DB Connection & Dependency Injection\n 18 | │   ├── main.py          # FastAPI App Entrypoint & CORS Middleware\n 19 | │   ├── models.py        # SQLAlchemy Declarative Models\n 20 | │   └── schemas.py       # Pydantic Schemas (V2)\n 21 | ├── .env.example         # Template for environment configuration\n 22 | ├── .gitignore           # Local development ignores\n 23 | ├── README.md            # Execution manual\n 24 | └── requirements.txt     # Python Dependencies\n 25 | ```\n 26 | \n 27 | ## Features\n 28 | \n 29 | - **Automated DB Bootstrap**: Automatically boots a local SQLite database (`gff_ai_local.db`) on application launch.\n 30 | - **Enterprise Logs**: A simple, high-performance database logger schema for auditing backend/frontend handshakes.\n 31 | - **Health Verification**: An endpoint at `/api/v1/health` that dynamically validates database status and platform health.\n 32 | - **Next.js Alignment**: Built-in CORS and request timing telemetry middleware matching frontend-dev requirements.\n 33 | - **Clean Interactive Specs**: Automatic redirect of root `/` path to the interactive OpenAPI UI (`/docs`).\n 34 | \n 35 | ---\n 36 | \n 37 | ## Local Setup & Run Guide\n 38 | \n 39 | ### 1. Prerequisites\n 40 | Ensure you have **Python 3.12+** and **pip** installed:\n 41 | ```bash\n 42 | python3 --version\n 43 | pip3 --version\n 44 | ```\n 45 | \n 46 | ### 2. Set Up Virtual Environment\n 47 | Move to the backend folder and create a clean Python virtual environment:\n 48 | ```bash\n 49 | cd backend\n 50 | python3 -m venv venv\n 51 | ```\n 52 | \n 53 | Activate the environment:\n 54 | - **macOS / Linux**:\n 55 |   ```bash\n 56 |   source venv/bin/activate\n 57 |   ```\n 58 | - **Windows**:\n 59 |   ```bash\n 60 |   venv\\Scripts\\activate\n 61 |   ```\n 62 | \n 63 | ### 3. Install Dependencies\n 64 | ```bash\n 65 | pip install -r requirements.txt\n 66 | ```\n 67 | \n 68 | ### 4. Set Up Environment Config\n 69 | Copy the example environment file:\n 70 | ```bash\n 71 | cp .env.example .env\n 72 | ```\n 73 | The defaults in `.env` are pre-tuned for seamless local development with the Next.js local frontend.\n 74 | \n 75 | ### 5. Run the Server\n 76 | Launch the development server via Uvicorn:\n 77 | ```bash\n 78 | uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000\n 79 | ```\n 80 | \n 81 | Once running, you can access:\n 82 | - **Interactive OpenAPI Documentation**: [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n 83 | - **Service Health Check Endpoint**: [http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health](http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health)\n 84 | \n 85 | ---\n 86 | \n 87 | ## API Documentation\n 88 | \n 89 | ### GET `/api/v1/health`\n 90 | Checks backend and database health.\n 91 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n 92 | ```json\n 93 | {\n 94 |   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n 95 |   \"timestamp\": 1719493200.0,\n 96 |   \"database\": {\n 97 |     \"status\": \"healthy\",\n 98 |     \"error\": null\n 99 |   },\n100 |   \"services\": {\n101 |     \"api\": \"healthy\",\n102 |     \"gff_core\": \"operational\"\n103 |   },\n104 |   \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n105 | }\n106 | ```\n107 | \n108 | ### GET `/api/v1/logs`\n109 | Returns the recent list of system log entries.\n110 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n111 | ```json\n112 | []\n113 | ```\n114 | \n115 | ### POST `/api/v1/logs`\n116 | Creates a test system log.\n117 | **Request Payload**:\n118 | ```json\n119 | {\n120 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n121 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n122 |   \"module\": \"handshake\"\n123 | }\n124 | ```\n125 | **Response (201 Created)**:\n126 | ```json\n127 | {\n128 |   \"id\": 1,\n129 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n130 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n131 |   \"module\": \"handshake\",\n132 |   \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T15:10:00.000000\"\n133 | }\n134 | ```","success":true}],"durationMs":3}}
